  "text": "In the ISFET, the underlying sensing principle relies on the change in the surface charge of the gate, which changes the gate voltage and modifies the operating characteristics of the FET device. Surface charge changes can also be detected using light. In a light-addressable potentiometric sensor (LAPS), the change in surface potential is detected by measuring a photo-induced current, and the surface charge depends on the pH of the fluid containing cells. A thorough review of the principles underlying LAPS can be found in [CITATION_1] .",
